        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 3 at 2:15PM MDT by NWS North Platte NE</headline>
        <description>At 214 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles northwest of Arthur, moving south at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Arthur, Sand Puddin Lake, Velma, and Jensen Lake.

This includes the following highways...
Highway 61 between mile markers 122 and 140.
Highway 92 between mile markers 165 and 170.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
